  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug-Bounty\r\n\r\n*Summary*: No message history until i type in the chat again after deletion\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nIf i deleted chat with a person i do see 2 possible options when i start chatting with him again:\r\n\r\n1. totally new chat is created and started with no history as i removed it (like Viber, Watsap)\r\n2. if we use offline inboxing and storing the messages they should appear immediately when i start the chat and not after i send new message there as this is confusing\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nNo message history until i type in the chat again after deletion\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open chat with Jarrad, send some messages, delete chat\r\n- Start the chat again and dont send anything there - no history\r\n- Send a message - history appears\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly 03/16/2018\r\n* Operating System: Android\r\n",
